observations.recommendation:
1) Direct the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant, General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of Road components for road projects;
2) Directs the General Services Officer to maintain the Local Road Network Property Card as prescribed by COA Circular 2015-008 for all roads and its components; and
Require the Municipal Accountant the following reporting procedures:
3) Prepare the Journal Entry Vouchers (JEVs) to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card, respectively. Support the JV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
4) Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road networks; and
5) Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

We recommended that the concerned officers strictly comply with the
provision of COA Circular No. 2013-004 on the requirement to submit
list of all on-going government projects/programs/activities and those that
are to be implemented during the year containing the following
information:
a. The project name;
b. Implementing unit, Office or division if it is not the agency as a
whole;
c. Brief description of the PPA;
d. Contractor or supplier, if any;
e. Mode of procurement;
f. Funding Source;
g. Cost of approve budget;
h. Project duration including start and completion date; and
j. Location

We further recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the
MPDO or Municipal Engineering Office to ensure that the Supervising
Auditor (SA) thru the Audit Team Leader (ATL) is informed within 10
days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of
the program/activity that the appropriate project signboards and or
public notices are already posted.

We recommended that Local Chief Executive:
a. Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit the required interim
financial statements, quarter reports on unliquidated cash advances;
and
b. Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to submit quarterly a Status of
Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (SAAOB);
